+
+## 14. Classic editor parity and retirement checkpoint
+
+The original Tkinter editor (`theme-editor.py`) is currently kept as a fallback
+for workflows that have not yet been fully migrated to the modern GTK editor.
+Before removing that fallback from the GTK UI or deleting the classic editor from
+the repository, run a final parity audit after the current roadmap work is
+complete.
+
+This checkpoint should happen **after** the current Video Inspector, media
+management, validation, preview, data-source, and canvas work has been reviewed.
+At that point, compare the classic editor again against the GTK editor and mark
+each item below as:
+
+- already implemented in GTK;
+- still needed and not migrated;
+- intentionally superseded by a better GTK workflow;
+- no longer needed.
+
+### 14.1. Required before hiding/removing the fallback
+
+The GTK editor should provide equivalent or better workflows for these classic
+editor capabilities before `Open Classic Editor` is removed from the GTK UI.
+
+#### Restore session
+
+The classic editor has an explicit session restore action that discards all
+changes made since the editor was opened.
+
+GTK requirement:
+- add a global `Restore session` action;
+- restore `theme_data` from `session_original`;
+- preserve atomic YAML saving;
+- clear or rebuild selection safely;
+- refresh preview, property panel, tree state, and Undo/Redo buttons;
+- keep the operation itself undoable when practical.
+
+Suggested UI location:
+
+```text
+⋮ → Restore session
+```
+
+#### Safe close behavior
+
+The classic editor asks what to do with unsaved/session changes when closing.
+
+GTK requirement:
+- detect when the current theme differs from `session_original`;
+- prompt before closing;
+- support:
+  - save and close;
+  - discard session changes and close;
+  - cancel and keep editing;
+- avoid leaving partially written YAML.
+
+#### Open theme YAML
+
+The classic editor can open the current `theme.yaml` directly.
+
+GTK requirement:
+- add an `Open theme.yaml` action;
+- open the exact current theme YAML path;
+- keep `Open Theme Folder` as a separate action.
+
+Suggested UI location:
+
+```text
+⋮ → Open theme.yaml
+⋮ → Open Theme Folder
+```
+
+#### Background image tools for selected elements
+
+The classic editor has contextual helpers for elements using `BACKGROUND_IMAGE`:
+
+- preview the configured background image;
+- preview the exact region used by the selected element when geometry exists;
+- open the background image in the file manager/default image viewer;
+- choose a new background image and copy it into the theme folder;
+- clear `BACKGROUND_IMAGE` from the selected element.
+
+GTK requirement:
+- add a contextual `Background image` section for eligible selected elements;
+- show a thumbnail/region preview;
+- expose `Choose image…`, `Open`, and `Clear` actions;
+- copy external images into the theme folder using safe names;
+- preserve Undo/Redo and atomic YAML save;
+- keep compatibility with shared video preview backgrounds.
+
+Suggested UI location:
+
+```text
+Selected element → Background image
+  [Preview]
+  [Choose image…] [Open] [Clear]
+```
+
+### 14.2. Do not port literally
+
+The classic editor's `Apply to display` action currently restarts the runtime
+process directly. The GTK editor should not copy that behavior as-is.
+
+Instead, replace it with the safer roadmap workflow:
+
+```text
+Validation pipeline
+→ Preview on display
+→ Keep or Restore
+```
+
+This means classic `Apply to display` is considered **superseded**, not missing.
+
+### 14.3. Safe retirement sequence
+
+When the required parity items above are implemented or explicitly superseded,
+retire the fallback in small steps:
+
+1. Remove `Open Classic Editor` from the GTK visible UI.
+2. Keep `theme-editor.py` in the repository for one extra cycle as a legacy
+   script that can still be run manually.
+3. Add a short deprecation note pointing users to `theme-editor-gtk.py`.
+4. After one stable release/checkpoint with no regressions, delete
+   `theme-editor.py` and any Tkinter-only documentation.
+
+Suggested branch:
+
+```text
+feature/theme-editor-classic-retirement
+```
+
+Suggested checkpoint commits:
+
+```text
+Add GTK session restore and close guard
+Add GTK background image element tools
+Deprecate classic theme editor fallback
+Remove classic theme editor
+```
